title: Get across the Dartford crossing by bike

heading_context: Get across the Dartford crossing by bike
chunks.html_content:
Ask for a special pick-up vehicle to take you and your bike through the Dartford crossing at Essex Point or Kent Point. You cannot cycle over the bridge or through the tunnel.

The service is free.

You cannot bring animals or e-scooters on this service.

You can turn up and use the service without booking if your bike fits on a car’s bike rack.

heading_context: Get across the Dartford crossing by bike
chunks.html_content:
Contact Connect Plus in advance if you’re in a group of more than 3 cyclists or to take a bike that will not fit on a car’s bike rack, for example:

  • tandems
  • bikes with a trailer

heading_context: Get across the Dartford crossing by bike
chunks.html_content:
1. Go to Kent Point or Essex Point.

  2. Follow signs pointing to a yellow telephone.

  3. Use the phone to request a pick-up. You do not need a number - it’s a direct line.

  4. Wait in the designated area.

A vehicle will arrive to take you and your bike through the crossing.
chunks.plain_content:
Get across the Dartford crossing by bike
How to use the service


Go to Kent Point or Essex Point.


Follow signs pointing to a yellow telephone.


Use the phone to request a pick-up. You do not need a number - it’s a direct line.


Wait in the designated area.


A vehicle will arrive to take you and your bike through the crossing.

heading_context: Get across the Dartford crossing by bike
chunks.html_content:
You can use the service 7 days a week, every day of the year, at these times:

  • 3am to 9am
  • 10:30am to 2pm
  • 3pm to 9pm
  • 10:30pm to 2am

There’s no service outside these times.

heading_context: Get across the Dartford crossing by bike
chunks.html_content: It usually takes around 15 minutes for the lift to arrive after you’ve called to request a pick up. It might take longer at rush hour or if there’s a traffic jam.
chunks.plain_content:

How long it takes
It usually takes around 15 minutes for the lift to arrive after you’ve called to request a pick up. It might take longer at rush hour or if there’s a traffic jam.
